Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed, no need to peel) then coarsely grate. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated). Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed, then thinly slice. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Mix the @mango chutney{40%g} with the @bulgogi sauce{75%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} and the @water for the sauce{1}(see ingredients for amount) in a #small bowl{}. Keep to one side. Finely chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}.

When the water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}. 

> Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} or #wok{} over medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and stir-fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. 

> Cook the chicken in batches to prevent it from stewing.

Transfer the chicken to a #bowl{} once cooked, then return the pan to the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add another drizzle of oil to your (now empty) pan if necessary. When hot, add the peppers. Stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the carrot, garlic and sauce, then bring to the boil. Once boiling, stir through the chicken and noodles. Toss to coat in the sauce and cook until everything is piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir frequently.

> Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Divide the stir-fry between your plates. Finish with a sprinkling of peanuts, coriander and chilli.

> Careful, the chilli is hot - add less if you don't like heat. Enjoy!